WEBVTT

00:01.133 --> 00:04.202
Cheers <i>is filmed</i>        
 <i>before a live studio audience.</i>

00:04.236 --> 00:05.453
All right,              
        here you go, Cliffie.

00:05.487 --> 00:06.655
How about       
                getting your mom

00:06.689 --> 00:08.623
a pair of these soothing,   
    gel-filled insoles,

00:08.658 --> 00:10.358
<i>and</i> odor eliminators.

00:10.392 --> 00:13.461
It's only her birthday,         
it's not Christmas.

00:13.495 --> 00:15.830
How about one of these
          Lucite snack trays

00:15.865 --> 00:17.832
that plays the theme
            from <i>Cats?</i>

00:17.867 --> 00:20.302
Yeah, Valentine's Day, 1963.

00:20.336 --> 00:23.038
Back then                       
it played "Exodus."

00:23.072 --> 00:24.705
Hummingbird feeder?

00:24.740 --> 00:27.525
Come on, you guys               
are just being silly            
now, right?

00:27.559 --> 00:28.827
Well, then, Cliff,
              I'm afraid

00:28.861 --> 00:32.330
you're going to spend   
        a little more than $1.99
        for your mom's gift.

00:32.363 --> 00:33.798
Yeah, you're right, Normie.

00:33.833 --> 00:35.300
You only turn 70 once.

00:36.602 --> 00:38.236
Speaking as a mom,

00:38.271 --> 00:39.671
you know, when        
          my kids give me gifts,

00:39.705 --> 00:41.572
the ones that always
            mean the most       
            to me are the ones

00:41.607 --> 00:42.941
they make themselves.

00:42.975 --> 00:46.611
For instance, look
              at this little    
              key chain here.

00:46.646 --> 00:49.680
Anthony made this for me the  
first year he went away to camp.

00:49.715 --> 00:52.117
I carried it with me
            ever since.

00:52.151 --> 00:54.835
I think it might be
             the most precious  
             thing I own.

00:54.870 --> 00:56.404
Well, I'll give you             
three bucks for it.

00:56.439 --> 00:58.473
Done.

